Context:
The goal is a visual regression check — if someone changes Menu or Select styles in the future, the side-by-side story immediately shows the drift.

Changes:

1. **Menu.stories.tsx** — Add a SideBySideWithSelect story:
```tsx
import { PermissionSelect } from '../ToolRow';

const SideBySideWithSelect: Story = {
  render: () => {
    const [perm, setPerm] = useState<'off' | 'ask' | 'auto'>('ask');
    return (
      <div className="flex items-start gap-8">
        <div>
          <p className="mb-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground">Menu dropdown</p>
          <Menu>
            <Menu.Trigger asChild>
              <Button size="sm">Open Menu</Button>
            </Menu.Trigger>
            <Menu.Content>
              <Menu.Item disabled className="text-muted-foreground">
                <Package className="h-3.5 w-3.5" />v0.1.0
              </Menu.Item>
              <Menu.Separator />
              <Menu.Item>Update to v0.2.0</Menu.Item>
              <Menu.Separator />
              <Menu.Item variant="destructive">Uninstall</Menu.Item>
            </Menu.Content>
          </Menu>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p className="mb-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground">Select dropdown</p>
          <PermissionSelect value={perm} onValueChange={setPerm} disabled={false} ariaLabel="Permission" />
        </div>
      </div>
    );
  },
};
```
Import `Package` from lucide-react and `useState` from react. Import `PermissionSelect` from `'../ToolRow'`.

2. **PluginMenu.stories.tsx** — Ensure the AllStates story already shows the destructive item without raw className (it should after US-001 cleans up PluginMenu.tsx). Add a `FullMenu` story with version + update + destructive all visible:
```tsx
const FullMenu: Story = {
  render: () => (
    <PluginMenu
      plugin={mockNpmPlugin({ update: { latestVersion: '0.2.0', updateCommand: 'npm update slack' } })}
      onUpdate={() => undefined}
      onRemove={() => undefined}
      updating={false}
      removing={false}
    />
  ),
  play: async ({ canvasElement }) => {
    const canvas = within(canvasElement);
    const trigger = canvas.getByLabelText('Plugin options');
    await userEvent.click(trigger);
    // Verify all three sections are visible
    await expect(screen.getByText('v0.1.0')).toBeVisible();
    await expect(screen.getByText(/Update to v0\.2\.0/)).toBeVisible();
    await expect(screen.getByText('Uninstall')).toBeVisible();
  },
};
```

Constraints:
- The SideBySideWithSelect story is for visual inspection — it does NOT need play assertions. Just render both dropdowns.
- Import paths must use the correct relative path (`'../ToolRow'` from stories in `components/`).
- Do NOT render both dropdowns open simultaneously — that requires complex portal management. Just show them both as trigger buttons, with a note to open each one to compare.
- Add necessary imports to the stories files: `useState`, `Package`, `PermissionSelect`.
